s the mean companion masses that we rule out of existence are\ngreater than 11.5 M$_{JUP}$ with an orbital period of 4 years and greater than\n7.5 M$_{JUP}$ with an orbital period of 8 years. Although we do not detect\ncompanions around our sub-sample of 12 stars, we demonstrate that our two\ntechniques probe a regime that is commonly missed in other companion searches\nof late type stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Jan 2015 23:05:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
