luters were more common in the more metal poor\nclusters. The statistically significant correlation of [Al/Fe] with [Si/Fe] in\nM15 suggests that $^{28}$Si leakage has occurred in this cluster. We also\npresent C, N and O abundances for stars cooler than 4500 K and examine the\nbehavior of A(C+N+O) in each cluster as a function of temperature and [Al/Fe].\nThe scatter of A(C+N+O) is close to its estimated uncertainty in all clusters\nand independent on stellar temperature. A(C+N+O) exhibits small correlations\nand anticorrelations with [Al/Fe] in M3 and M13, but we cannot be certain about\nthese relations given the size of our abundance uncertainties. Star-to-star\nvariations of $\\alpha-$elements (Si, Ca, Ti) abundances are comparable to our\nestimated errors in all clusters.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Jan 2015 11:05:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 22 Jan 2015 18:57:37 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 4 Apr 2015 11:18:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
